.\" %W% %G%
.TH Dscreen 2D D-language
.SH NAME
Dscreen \- Clears the entire screen, creates a full-screen window, and chooses this as the current window
.br
.I (D Language Tool)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Dscreen
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Dscreen
is a one-step macro which:
.nf
    Clears the entire screen,
    Creates a new window which fills the entire screen,
    Chooses this new window to be the current window.
.fi

To perform these three actions individually, the user can run the GRASS
commands \fIDclear.screen, Dnew\fR, and \fIDchoose\fR, respectively.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.TS
ll.
\fIDINTRO[2D]\fR	Introduction to the GRASS \fID\fR tools
.br
.sp
\fIDchoose[2D]\fR	To choose a window to be the current window
.br
\fIDclear.screen[2D]\fR	T{
To clear the entire screen and memory of all existing windows
T}
.br
\fIDnew[2D]\fR	To create new graphics windows on the screen
.TE
.SH "AUTHOR"
James Westervelt, U.S. Army Construction Engineering Research Laboratory
